### GET - List all tasks
GET http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks
Accept: application/json

### GET - List completed tasks only
GET http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks?completed=true
Accept: application/json

### GET - Get specific task
GET http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/1
Accept: application/json

### GET - Get non-existent task (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/999
Accept: application/json

### POST - Create new task
POST http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test new task",
  "description": "Created via HTTP client",
  "completed": false
}

### POST - Create task without title (should return 400)
POST http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Task without title - should fail"
}

### PUT - Update existing task
PUT http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated task title",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "completed": true
}

### PUT - Update non-existent task (should return 404)
PUT http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This will fail",
  "completed": true
}

### DELETE - Delete task
DELETE http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/2

### DELETE - Delete non-existent task (should return 404)
DELETE http://localhost:9001/api/v1/tasks/999